recordings.file-name: XC351440-KOHLMEISE, Strophentypwechsel  27.04.2015  Lörrach, Finkenweg  05_53  VOC_150427-2481   Teil 2  gült. neu.mp3
recordings.rmk:
continuation from XC351439:
The Tit sings 5 other types of verses (Strophentypen nach Bergmann) with changing motives, rhythm and pitches (Tonhöhen)
4 – fourth type of verse: 50 verses,  to 5:27, each verse with nearly the same motive 3-9 times repeated (mostly, 23x, 6 times)  
5 – fifth type of verse : 66 verses, from 5:21 to 11:24, each verse with the same motive, which is similar to a Coal Tit's song,   1- 9 times repeated (mostly, 29x, 6 times)
6 – sixth type of verse: from 11:25 to 11:50, only 3 verses  
7 – seventh type of verse: from 12:02 to 12:14, only 4 verses. At 12:11 only one motive, similar to the second type (in XC351439)
12:15 alarm call
8 – eigth type of verse: from 12:20 to 12:52, each verse with nearly the same motive, 7 times repeated.
From 5:28 a second Great Tit in the background begins to answer.
At least the Tit flies into a garden with a lot of trees, where I cannot see it all the time, so I am not sure, if the last 3 types of verses have been sung by one individuum, or,  if one ore two types have been sung from a second individuum, coming into the foreground.

recordings.file-name: XC351439-KOHLMEISE, Strophentypwechsel 27.04.2015  Lörrach, Finkenweg  5_53  VOC_150427-2481 - Teil 1 gült. neu.mp3
recordings.rmk:
the Tit sings 3 types of verses (Strophentypen nach Bergmann) with changing motives, rhythm and pitches (Tonhöhen)
1- first type of verse: only 5 verses, because the Tit`s singing was in full swing, when I began to record
2 – second type of verse: 57 verses, from 0:39 to 6:04, each verse with the same motive 3-8 times repeated (mostly, 30x, 5 times)
3 – third type of verse: 60 verses, from 6: 07 to 11:31, each verse with the same motive, 3-6 times repeated (mostly, 42x, 4 times).
